text:
Queenie Shu-Ying Hsiao is a multidisciplinary designer (NYU ITP  HCI).
She blends visual storytelling, design systems, and playful interactions.
Recent work: Uber  Low Price Insights; Lume  independent fashion marketplace.
Roles: Product/Visual/UI Design (NYC/hybrid).
Contact: email & LinkedIn in site footer.

Uber  Pricing Insights for Grocery & Retail
Highlight when groceries are cheaper than average so shoppers can make smarter choices.
Uber  Pricing Insights for Grocery & Retail  Designed a pricing insights feature to surface when items are below typical prices.
Uber  Pricing Insights for Grocery & Retail  Explored messaging framework variants and thresholds by collaborating with Content Design team.
Uber  Pricing Insights for Grocery & Retail  Collaborated with cross-functional teams from Product Management, Content Design, Data Science, and Engineering.

Lume  Marketplace for Independent Designers
Help independent fashiondesigners gain visibility in a saturated market.

Lume  Marketplace for Independent Designers  Independent fashion designers often have trouble getting discovered in a saturated market. They lack the resources, marketing power, and established platform exposure that larger brands have.

Lume  Marketplace for Independent Designers  Conducted 8 user interviews, competitive analysis, and brainstorming sessions to ideate on the product. Then validated the final prototpye with 10 people total in 2 rounds of tesitng.

Lume  Marketplace for Independent Designers  Lume combines curated search filters, social-style feeds, and shoppable moodboards to create meaningful connections between designers and audiences. For designers, Lume offers performance insights and simple tools to track orders, revenue, and engagement. For shoppers, it provides clear ways to explore by material, color, or concept, as well as inspiration through user-generated outfits and curated boards.

FlowFi  DeFi Liquidity Management Tool
Help crypto investors manage and optimize liquidity across decentralized finance platforms.
FlowFi  DeFi Liquidity Management Tool  DeFi investors often struggle with fragmented tools, unclear performance tracking, and high barriers to understanding liquidity positions across protocols.

FlowFi  DeFi Liquidity Management Tool  Conducted in-depth whitepaper research and competitive analysis of existing DeFi protocols to identify gaps in liquidity management. Used these insights to shape user flows and simplify portfolio tracking, then validated the final prototype through peer feedback during the hackathon.

FlowFi  DeFi Liquidity Management Tool  FlowFi provides a dashboard that consolidates liquidity positions, real-time performance insights, and automated strategies to optimize returns. It reduces complexity for investors while giving them confidence and transparency in managing assets.

UX Club NYU  Cofounder, Brand Identity & Visual System
Cofounded the club and created a clear, approachable visual system across touchpoints.
UX Club NYU  Cofounder, Brand Identity & Visual System  Cofounded UX Club NYU and established the brand identity and visual system.
UX Club NYU  Cofounder, Brand Identity & Visual System  Led a small team to produce posters, event materials, and social templates for consistency.
UX Club NYU  Cofounder, Brand Identity & Visual System  Crafted a recognizable system across print and digital that feels clear, vibrant, and approachable.

Q: Who is Queenie Hsiao?
A: I'm Queenie Shu-Ying Hsiao  a product designer who makes simplicity feel exciting again. I started in Fashion Design at Parsons, then shifted into HumanComputer Interaction at NYU's Interactive Telecommunications Program. I've designed at Uber, and co-founded the UX Club @ NYU where I currently am president, blending storytelling, interaction, and visual systems into playful but clear experiences.

Q: What roles are you looking for?
A: Product Design roles in NYC, open to hybrid, in-person, or remote opportunities.

Q: How do I contact you?
A: Email or LinkedIn in my site footer  happy to chat!

Q: Where have you worked at?
A: I previously interned at Uber and am currently President of NYU's UX Club.

Q: Whats your design focus?
A: I focus on visual UI and UX design, crafting interactions that make simplicity feel exciting again. I love blending clarity with delight in every project.

Q: What are your core skills?
A: UI/UX design, interaction design, visual design, design systems, AI products, storytelling, and design strategy.

Q: What tools do you use?
A: My main toolkit includes Figma, dscout, Adobe Creative Suite (Illustrator, Photoshop, After Effects, Premiere Pro), Protopie, Origami, and Cursor.

Q: What's the UX Club?
A: UX Club is a student-run organization focused on building a community for product designers at NYU, I co-founded the club in 2024 and currently serve as president. I wanted to create a community of design focused individual who wanted to connect with industry professionals and learn from other students. I oversee all aspects of the club, but mainly focus on events and design. We host speaker events, run mentorship socials, and organize a design-a-thon  creating both the experiences and the visuals that bring the community together.

Q: What inspires your design?
A: Im inspired by minimalism, delight, and anything that feels exciting  experiences that are simple, clear, and spark joy.

Q: How do you approach projects?
A: I start by framing the problem, researching users, and sketching flows. Then I refine into high-fidelity UI systems and test iteratively. I collaborate closely with PMs, engineers, and researchers to balance clarity with delight.
